Step three: You may think that you don't need all these packages and you are right, but don't have they installed on your computer dont'n will make you better
Some packages are from AUR, but if you install the chaotic-aur repository you will don't have any problem to install it with pacman
Or you can install trizen or yay and install all aur-packages from aur repository

Step four: copy the content of config directory to your config directory

Step five: I take years stolen the betters wallpapers on internet and this selections of wallpaper have gens, and a lot of wallpapers that is disgosting and I dont know why I dont delete they yet
Copy the wllpaper directory to your pictures path and make an favor to youself, delete half of these wallpapers. May the force guide you to chose wisely.

Step six: Start basics services, if you use systemd run

systemclt enable sddm
systemclt enable NetworkManager
systemclt enable Bluetooth
systemctl enable coolercontrold

If you dont use systemd... ... ... ... sory, I dont know how to help you

Step seven: Up the firewall, just run
ufw enable

Step eight: This far is suposed that you have an user created, an password configured and don't forget to create the grub config before restart the system...

Step nine: Restart the computer, is much easyer

